"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is setting both major locator and xticks for the x-axis. When using a major locator, it's not necessary to set xticks manually. Setting xticks manually will override the major locator. In this case, using a MonthLocator is more suitable for date data.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\\n\"\n}"